    "1266172253117592007/10/20 13:53:28jiyoungleI pulled a spider towards the guards and the quest disappeared for me.  I just tried this on Oct. 20, 2007.  The gold question mark was there for a second, then disappeard, then reappeared for another second.  I tried clicking, but nothing happened.  So, I ended up abandoning the quest and running back to Theramore.  If this happens to you, you will have to find Archmage Tervosh on Theramore Isle and not at Sentry Point.  He is at the top of the main tower (66, 49).",
    "126675985317592007/05/01 09:08:33sharnlaWorks like a dream. Don't forget to damage Heindel while pulling him, or he will run back. I had to abandon and wait for him to respawn after that.\
\
Also, using a pet to pull the mob to guards seems to yield some... unexpected results. Regardless, if you run to the friendly guards with Heindel fighting your pet, as long as *you* are near the guards, they will aggro your pet's target (assuming pet attack is on), even if the pet is still quit far (and yes, you can make the guards come back too, by giving pet follow command, it's kind of fun). ^^",
    "12667594007592006/09/20 05:41:52peeweeswedenThis quest is also one of those \"easily soloable even without the proper level requirements\". \
\
What you do is this: (I did this as lvl 36 warrior and didn't even sweat about it, I assume anyone at lvl 28-30 could do it)\
\
Before you accept this quest, pull a swamp mob or two into the guards. They will be very busy. Accept the quest and strafe or back to the nearest tower. If you don't keep hitting Hendel, he will drop you and run back to the camp. When you get close to the tower, the guards there will assist you. When Hendel reaches about 25% health, he will give up and run back to the camp. If the guards there are still aggroed at you, pull them towards the tower as well, let the guards there deal with them. \
\
You will get 6400 XP, a gold and 30 silver, and a nice little ring from the cute miss Proudmoore upon completion. Nice, for a few minutes of work, huh?",
    "1266144460101444602007/08/26 17:35:59bEwaReSuch an easy quest. I did it as lvl 33 lock.\
The way i did it, and it could be done at lower lvls with lock.\
Recieve quest, when they all start attacking you do Suffering so VW takes all the aggro. I didnt want to risk lossing VW so i feared one guard. While you do all that it will pass about 4-5 secs and VW will do 2x Torment on the Private Hendel. Basicaly it means you will be able to nuke Hendel and not to be afraid of getting the aggro of VW. Hendel down to 25-33% and turns friendly as well as the guards. Jaina, that Mage dude and one more guard teleports to you. Finish quest gain easy 500 aliance rep and +250 Stormwind. Also over 6k exp :)",
    "1266188751201887512007/11/21 07:31:33SpaldingDate Completed : 11/21/07\
WoW Version : 2.3\
Player Level : 28 (protection/holy paladin)\
Method : Solo\
\
1) Pull a mob into the camp (I used a Withervine Ripper from across the road).\
2) The guards at Hendel's camp will aggro against the mob and defend you.  Stop attacking the mob, and wait for the guards to knock the mob down to roughly 25% health.\
3) Talk to Private Hendel and accept quest to subdue him.  Start fighting Hendel.\
4) When the guards finish off the mob above, they will turn on Hendel and finish him off for you.  Once the guards begin with Hendel, you really only need to worry about keeping yourself alive.  When the gaurds took over, I did nothing offensive and simply healed myself as Hendel does not aggro to guards, he will remain focused on you.\
5) Once subdued, the guards stop attacking and reset, Lady Proudmoore shows up, along with Archmage Tervosh.  When quest is complete, talk to Tervosh as soon as you can.\
6) After completing quest, if you respond quickly, you can also turn in the final quest to Lady Proudmoore before she disappears back to her tower.\
\
I never really fell below 50% health while Hendel was attacking me.  This method works great.  Other classes may have a bit more difficulty taking direct hits from Hendel, but the overall strategy above should work for everyone (in my opinion).\
\
Good luck",
