  ["Attack on the Tower39"] = {
    "69613932npcSkuerto2789npcSkuerto27893000Ironforge2501694269536964697",
    "696193410101934102007/11/29 13:36:03Ajariaalso new in patch 2.3: the mobs are no longer elite, but there has been added several mobs on the slope up to the tower - there's now 5 where there used to be 2, so making the quest a little tricky still, but it's all in all easier, just completed it as 38 shadow priest..",
    "696185455111816472007/11/15 23:54:58ContayI was [i]really[/i] hoping that this quest would be easier after the 2.3 patch, but unfortunately it wasn't.  The Boulderfist Lords in specific still hit for a LOT of damage, and the Summoned Guardians are ineffective.\
\
Just do this quest naked and corpse-run it.  If you do at least that (and Spirit-res afterwards -- taking 25% item damage as opposed to 50-60% item damage is preferable), it makes the new rewards a lot more worth it.",
    "6964388740438872007/02/28 09:43:05XathrusAs you work your way up the tower that will be a box on each level. After opening a box and taking the object out several mobs will spawn (3 for the first, 4 for the next, and 5 for the last).",
    "696176167101761672007/10/28 21:06:06KashimDid this as a 41 Combat Rogue.\
\
I didnt fight any Ogres what i did was every time i past a ogre i would sap him, when i got to the Boxes i would make sure any ogres would not attack me when i came out of stealth, i un-stealthed waited untill my Stealth cool down was around half way, looted the box and re stealthed.\
\
This for me worked as a treat hope it works for you rogues out there",
    "696206954102069542007/12/25 05:58:44jerrybluntJust solo'd this as a lvl 36 fire Mage. Used the die and return method, had no problems. Just wait till the right moment, rezz, sheep if needed open box. Fight die and a quick corpse run back. Repeat at each target. Not really in the spirit of the game I guess but gets good results. lol",
    "696181647101816472007/11/09 17:44:44KneahiWas able to do solo this as a 35 lock on PTR, due to all the mobs in Stromgarde being made non-elite.\
\
Did the same run, die, rez thing as stated above;  saves time to have a soulstone up so you can just rez as soon as its safe.  Didn't have any difficulties with mob pats, either.",
    "696185836101858362007/11/16 15:23:24ozmentationsjust a little sidenote: as you go down the ramp by the trolls entering the part with the ogres, there is a little post on the right hand sid with a kind of straw X on it, if you jump onto the ledge right by there you can cruise all the way round to the tower without the hassle of killing all the ogres on the way to it...\
\
saves looooads of time =)",
    "6969836410983642007/06/05 01:24:39trinamsfi just did it as a 38 warrior...just run and die and respwan at each box....easy peasy",
    "6968717520871752007/05/22 02:19:45adriangarsideI tried the repetitive dieing approach. It worked even better than above. I bubbled standing on a raised section just diagonally across from the tower with divine shield (10s) and ran into the tower. I didn't see the first crate and ended up running past it up to the 2nd floor. At that point all the mob chasing me had given up. I accidentally aggro'd the ogre that is very near the 2nd crate (I could've avoided that if I'd been thinking faster) but by healing I was able to dispatch him without too much difficulty. Then I opened the crate and immediately ran up to the top floor. I lost all the newly spawned mob by doing that so I could immediately open the 3rd crate. At that point I tried to lose them by dropping all the way down the tower. I'm not sure how many lost but I think I still had several one me at the bottom of the tower. I didn't really try very hard to stay alive but I doubt I would have managed it if I had. So as a ghost I ran back in, found the crate I'd missed (took a bit of looking). Respawned by it, opened it immediately and then immediately ran out of the tower and bubbled as I left. That let me escape all the way to the alliance section with only the final ogre right by that section still aggroing me. Since I had plenty of mana I healed myself and killed him off (without any help from those lazy alliance soldiers I might add - they ignored the hulking great ogre in the middle of their camp!).\
\
So one death and only 2 ogre kills (ignoring the several I killed to get near the tower) to quickly get all the items as a lvl 44 palladin is a resounding success.",
    "6964656510465652007/03/05 13:03:23McVaghSolo-able if ur a rogue. I suggest being level 40 and Imp Sap helps.\
Simply sneak in, locate box, sap ogre, open her up, and vanish to avoid the numerous ogres that pop up.\
\
The first one is the trickiest as there is two ogres that pass by it.\
\
Funny thing is the ogres I made pop up never left as far as I know, so there is 3-5 ogres just sitting around the chests,sucks to be the group trying to do that.",
    "696203650102036502007/12/18 23:20:19Psycovaafter 2.3 what I did as a 39 warrior was grab the first chest and ran as best as i could to the top floor where the 3rd chest is (you can use the pathways to los the mobs a bit and buy more time to go around them and all the way up)  Run back and grab the 3rd chest and immediately jump over the railing behind you and go down and grab the second chest.\
\
Now its all about luck and getting out of there.  Jump all the way down and activate shield wall or put up something to protect you (hunters can use your pets to the best advantage and shamans use your slowing totems) and go the entrance of the tower.  Turn left, and left again immediately and you should see like a cauldren and a fire.  There's a place where the wall meets the tower straight ahead and just wall jump (jump so you get stuck kinda between the wall and the tower) and climb up there.  From there everything just evades and if you run along that wall there's a crack which you can go out of and follow all the way around to the front of Stromgarde.\
\
This is just so you only have to die once and it saves time (not having to run back)",
    "696208490102084902007/12/28 00:46:06pentagonevery time you open a box, a shaman and a mauler will spawn, so be prepared.",
