    "10351062332201062332007/06/17 23:15:47DrexxisSo many people have asked why they can't get quests from this guy so many times that thought it best to just write a guide. Enjoy!\
\
There is a series of quests you have to do, here is the order and locations:\
\
1) Bathran's Hair (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1010) - The guy is located at Maestra's Post, you collect the items from Plant Bundle's which are found to the north of the Post, on the east side of the path.\
\
2) Orendil's Cure (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1020) - Go to Pelturas Whitemoon in the little house by the south bridge in Astranaar.\
\
3) Elune's Tear (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1033) - Head out of Astranaar via the south path and follow the path until you come across a small slit of water on the north side of the path. On the west side of the water slit there is a subtle path on the ground that lead to where the Tear's are. Follow the path up while eliminating all enemies. The tear's are on the small island in the middle of the water body. ( An alternate way to the place is a shortcut path near the graveyard to the South-East or Astranaar.)\
\
4) The Ruins of Stardust (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1034) - Head out of Astranaar from the south. You'll see a smaller path that branches off the main path on the right side. Follow it. Keep heading that direction and you'll soon walk in between two statues, and if you keep going the air will turn a pale yellow-green. There is an island in the water in that area. You collect the quest object off the sparkling plants on that island.\
\
5) Hand in that quest and it'll leave you hear at the quest \"Fallen Sky Lake.\" You've got a decent walk ahead of you for this one. Follow the main path from the south Astranaar exit until you come to a large T crossroad, if you left from Astranaar this T crossroad will come after you cross the bridge over the river, not before where Raynewood retreat is. Head south towards The Barrens, but keep an eye to the West side of the path. There will be a small pond. You have to kill the level 30 Shadethicket Oracle, which is usually on the small island in the pond. Collect the Moonstone and return to claim your reward.\
\
I hope this helps some of you.",
