    "694132104501321042007/08/04 10:14:48lifelivenowFor those of you that are like me and don't actually know how to get to the tower: \
\
When you are standing facing Stromgarde turn  to the right. Don't actually go inside. Follow the wall outside as closely as you can until you get to the coordinates (21.3, 70.5) Be careful to not fall off ;) You can walk the wall inside, but do watch out because there is a patrol that walks up there as well.",
    "694195466111321042007/12/03 14:29:51marcx77Coming from Refuge Pointe or Hammerfall, the shorter way is clockwise around Stromgarde. No need to hug the wall. You can climb up the hill right before the path breaks left towards a cave, right on the edge of the water and right below the hole in the wall. It takes a bit of jumping and moving around, but it can be done. Walk up on the right side of the slope and jump when you get \"stuck\".",
    "694185617111321042007/11/16 07:17:56aiyaconfirmed ... 21, 70 ... there is a break in the wall and you can skip all the mobs at the front of the castle.\
\
Also want to highlight the fact that this gap is accessible ONLY if you go counter-clockwise around the castle. The steepness of the hills prevent you from climbing up to the walls if you go clock-wise.",
    "694179695101796952007/11/05 16:52:50ohboisolo'd quite easily as a lvl 40 demonology warlock. i just pulled using curse of agony, ran back holding cntrl+2 to keep my VW close and once he was far enough away sent in my VW and went to town. just make sure to take time in between each to heal and mana up. i got a lot of XP doing it on my own, 400-700xp per mob. once i got what i needed i mounted and got out of there. pretty easy, just make sure you pull.",
    "694189881101898812007/11/23 09:48:41HawlinQuest now gives 4150 Exp as of Patch 2.3.",
    "694160108201601082007/09/28 23:53:56TiemujinWhen you come in to Stromgarde take a right into the alliance friendly area, then a left right before you go under the archway and there you have it. The above way works and is the way i came in but this way tends to be easier.",
    "6941536840153682006/12/14 05:56:04kanaxyaFirst you have to do \"Worth its Weight in Gold\" quest from Apprentince Kryten, then you have to do \"Wand Over Fist\" from the guy near him and then you can get this quest.\
