    "96899968110996812007/06/06 18:08:33PingaNot sure if they changed it, but I found this quest extremelly hard to solo as a 19 mage. He have a lot more than 980 hp as shown here, and moves really fast, making impossible to just kite. After 3 fireballs and some fire blasts left him still 90%.",
    "9689206679112049192007/12/24 16:54:59ninjaDXOR just use a Tremor Totem and Earth Shock his Dragon Breath casting. No shaman should have any problems with this quest, even if you solo it.",
    "968946363131428242007/03/05 04:47:16SupapowatymePiece of advice for the fast respawns, dont loot the bodies till after the fight, that should make sure those whelps dont respawn.",
    "9689202750102027502007/12/17 07:53:45KumarenNazjatarPopped retaliation as a 20 fury warrior, probably wouldn't have needed to if i was draenei. Ended up with about 15% hp, not the easiest quest ever but the rewards are good.",
    "96898174250817422007/05/12 06:12:27cjonesctNote that when you click on the bonfire, the Bundle of Dragon Bones is taken from your inventory, so if you die without killing him, you will have to abandon the quest and get it again from Prince Toreth to get another bundle of bones with which to summon Razormaw.",
    "96892131240213122007/01/18 10:27:30KriL3Soloed him easily with my 19 shaman.",
    "9689147732211465562007/09/01 16:14:24DarovThis is a fairly easy quest, Is soloable but super easy with 2. Decent rewards in my opinion. Worth doing.",
    "9689138283511183902007/08/15 10:21:00PaeganI suggest you follow your own advice re thinking before you post.\
\
Many people -are- interested in other's experiences. When I lookup a group quest here I want to know if I really need 2 people or if I can solo it, because I'm not levelling by running around with a healbot or high-level help. Your worthless 'giev coordz nowz' post contributes nothing.\
