2. Aturk the Anvil - Ogrimmar at blacksmith area\
Learn Orcish War Leggings pattern.\
3. Ox <The Mithril Order> Ogrimmar at blacksmith area (starts the whole Mithril Order quests line)\
Sends you to Booty Bay to meet McGavan, and gives you a trinket (requires Blacksmithing skill 210)\
4. McGavan <The Mithril Order> Booty Bay at blacksmith area\
Sends you to meet Galvan the Ancient in Stranglethorn Vale\
5. Galvan the Ancient - <Artisan Blacksmith of the Mithril Order>\
Located in Stranglethorn Vale at 50,20. Teaches 3 Ornate Mithril patterns, and sends you to his pupil Trenton Lightammer in Gadgetzan. Also gives you a better trinket (hope you kept the 1st one) called Signet of Expertise which summons the temporary Hammer of Expertise  (purple item).\
6. Trenton Lighthammer <The Mithril Order> Gadgetzan at blacksmith area\
Teaches you 3 more Ornate Mithril patterns (helm, breastplate, boots).\
Upon completion your are inducted into the Mithril Order which he announces in /yell chat.  You receive the Glimmering Mithril Insignia trinket, which required blacksmithing 225.\
\
So, after all those I think I'm ready to choose Armorsmith or Weaponsmith.  Hope this also helped you to know who to look for.",
    "52835282830528282007/03/17 19:03:04fongIs it possible to just buy the Ornate Mithril stuff from someone who can make it? The pieces are usually up on the AH for fairly cheap.",
    "52835946421528282007/03/29 23:42:30AnvilYes it is, I used to charge people 1/3 the price of the mithril needed to do the turn-ins to craft their Armorsmith items. Quite a good way to make money.",
    "5283150568311442442007/09/08 05:49:22BadgerBoyI found that I couldn't get the quest from Hank until my Blacksmithing was at 225.  I went to him first time and it was 211.  Got it up to 225 and hey presto, he had a ! above his head.",
    "528320593130205932007/01/14 12:19:59salvation122Total mats for the entire quest line:\
\
286 Mithril Bars\
70 Iron Bars\
25 Truesilver Bars\
30 Coal\
36 Heavy Stone\
36 Solid Stone\
18 Mageweave Cloth\
14 Thick Leather\
4 Citrine\
2 Aquamarine\
1 Heart of Fire\
\
I strongly reccommend you either get friends and guildmates to help contribute mats or buying some Mithril off the auction house; otherwise you'll be on this questline forever. Aside from forging legendaries, this is probably one the most expensive questlines in mat costs in the entire game - and to be perfectly honest, it's largely not worth it without getting some good world-drop patterns unless your guild is going to funnel you the mats to get reputation so you can craft resist armor for them.",
    "528317683180176832006/12/21 03:29:11InfinityXHow to become an Armorsmith:\
When you have your Blacksmith skills up to a certain value, \"expert\"  I think, when you talk to the BS trainer in IF choices will pop up that say- tell me more about \"weaponsmith\" or \"armorsmith\".\
\
For Armorsmith you:\
1. Declare Armorsmith\
2. You will be directed to the other Dwarf by the forge about the specifics of being an Armorsmith. He gives you a quest requiring that you make 7 items: 4 ornate mithril helmets, 2 ornate mithril boots, 1 ornate mithril breast plate. But guess what?  This quest is the tip of the iceberg. You don't have the recipes for these items, they are not on the BS training list, and he does not tell you where to go or who to talk to!\
3. You talk to  Hank the Hammer  in Stormwind and complete his quest, which will open up the quest to talk to the guy in BB (by the forge outside) part of the Mithril order.\
4. Talk to guy in BB who then directs you to talk to a Dwarf out in the wilderness of STV. (north of the ogre mound)\
5. Gavan (in the wilderness) will have 3 quests, to get a certain amount of mithril bars, iron bars, citrine, etc. Each quest you complete gives you a recipe.\
6. He will then direct you to his student (by the forge inside) studying in Gadgetzan.\
7. This student will have 3 more quests, that give you more recipes.  After each quest you get more recipes. At this point you are still missing the ornate mithril helmet recipe.\
8. So you go to Gadgetzan, in Tanaris and talk to the Night Elf at the Forge in town. He has 3 quests which get you more recipes. One of those is the ornate mithril helmet.\
9. After all of this you'll have all the recipes you need to complete the original quest: The Art of Armorsmith.\
10. Now it's JUST a matter of working your tail off collecting more raw material to make the 7 items. When all is said and done you get approx 3900 XP for the original quest- The Art of Armorsmith, and a pat on the back, besides having some top notch armor. The the potential to make more.",
    "52836106730610672007/04/02 12:55:54JessikkaOne thing that's not mentioned is that Hank the Hand won't talk to you unless you have 210 Blacksmithing, that caused a lot of confusion, especially considering the Armorsmithing quest is available at 200.",
