  ["Ur's Treatise on Shadow Magic28"] = {
    "193812826npcHigh Sorcerer Andromath5694npcHigh Sorcerer Andromath56942300119392193831940",
    "19383572650357262007/02/14 06:44:54zgonSoloed as 28 lvl fire mage. Pretty easy. You just need to be carefull.   \
When you get to the top floor the book is on the left from the ramp (on the shelf). Keep to the left side of the ramp and you should not aggro Morganth.\
\
Cords of tower: 79, 48",
    "1938127052211254752007/07/26 08:18:48kaTTooThat's nice, if you have all those immenities.  Personally, I don't have all those, yet.\
\
I have a level 26 Mage and solo'd this quite well.  I do admit that I died twice during this quest, but it was worth it to get the book.  You have to kill or escape the three outside guards, and when you get close to the inside, you will have a rogue gnoll and a shadowcaster to deal with. As soon as you attack the shadowcaster,  you will have one of the demon dogs come after you from above.  I sheeped the gnoll, took care of the demon dog and then battled the shadowcaster and finished him off.  Once I headed up the stairs,  I was met by an `entourage of demon dogs and gnolls,  I kept running up the staircase until they killed me; came back and rez'd in a safe place just right of the top of the stairs (where there is a cove).  If you are careful,  you will not aggro Morganth.  However, before you rez, you might want to scope the book case just to the left and across from the staircase, on the bottom shelf where the book is.  Once I rez'd and mana-up'd, I sheeped the gnoll. As the demon dogs started running for me,  I used frost nova on both of them.  I ran to the bookcase and got the book.  After that,  I didn't care if they killed me. I had the book. As a matter of fact,  I didn't even put up a fight. I let them kill me and took rez sickness at the gy. My repairs were around 14s. \
\
I'm sure you can do this without dying.  But it didn't bother me to do it this way.  \
\
Good luck on your quest.",
    "1938125475101254752007/07/23 10:57:19SugarwoodEasy enough to solo, but you only have to die once really.\
\
Pop Mana Shield, run up to the top of the tower, using Cone of Cold and Frost Nova all the while.  Die right on the stairs, then run back to your corpse.  There's a side of the top level that is empty, rez there, buff, mana up, and get ready.  Sheep the gnoll, attack the dogs.  Use Cone of Cold before they get to you, then use Frost Nova if you need to (I was a Frost Mage, so they got stuck on the CoC).  Take them down from there.  The secret to this fight is using everything you've got.  Keep the other guy sheeped, and use Couterspell on the dogs when they use Mana Drain.\
\
I got done with the two dogs just a couple of seconds after the gnoll unsheeped.  I shielded, sheeped the gnoll again, and killed the last dog (remember to use Blizzard here, it works).  After the dogs are down, it's very easy.  Use Evocation while the gnoll is sheeped, and then start off with a Pyro or Fireball then following it up with a Fireblast, and a Counterspell when he starts casting.  Then Frost Nova, and it's over for him.",
    "19384012311357262007/02/21 19:38:16PhrostySolo'd at a 27 Frost Mage, the dogs inside can cast Mana Burn that takes away about 200 mana, I believe. You should be able to counterspell it in time, but I'd bring a mana pot or two just in case.",
    "1938147988201479882007/09/02 06:06:45ookluhNot sure what all the fuss was about.. read up on the quest here, and thought it would be difficult to figure out.  28 Fire Mage, most gear still from pre and early 20s.  Got to the top of the ramp and saw them - no aggro yet, so.. I opened with Pyroblast on a dog, followed with Fireball, then Fire Blast and my wand to kill it.  Sheeped gnoll.  Killed other dog with Fire Blast and Scorch.  Pyroblasted the sheep, fireball, fire blast, wand.  All 3 dead - no pots, no shield, no mana agate, no evocation needed.. it did take me down to about 10% health and mana, but that could be easily overcome by using any of the aforementioned resources.",
    "1938653106532006/09/18 14:08:19DaerionYou do NOT have to kill Morganth in the tower to get the book.  Fight up to the top and grab the  book from a shelf opposite his coterie and you'll be fine.  There's a gnoll and a couple of familiars in front of it, but you should be able to sheep one, kill one, and jump down to buy time to kill the last one.  Bandage/evoke while it runs down.",
