    "261182149101821492007/11/10 22:54:14fushiryoDid this as a 38 rogue.\
\
Undead Ravagers don't pick up on stealthed characters, and they don't hit very hard once you've entered combat. I guess having being eyeless, weaponless, and made of rotting bone makes life hard. Sucks for them, but at 215 xp each, they are probably the best xp/time ratio of any mob at this level that I've seen.\
\
As a rogue I used cheap shot, waited for the stun effect to wear off, then hit them with three sinister strikes all in a row followed by an eviscerate. After all this they usually didn't last long enough for my energy to recharge enough for another sinister strike.\
\
The Necromancers can make things difficult, as they summon undead ravagers to their side. If you've got it, a kick or a quick shield bash makes things much easier, but character classes with area of effect attacks may find it more expedient to just let them summon. ymmv.\
