  ["Mor'Ladim35"] = {
    "22813528npcCommander Althea Ebonlocke264npcCommander Althea Ebonlocke2642050Stormwind15012252227322842295231",
    "2286141660614162007/04/03 05:25:32ParynI was able to solo Mor'Ladim as a level 33 shadow priest, without using potions or anything special. Well, I used the Draenei racial symbol of hope, but after you read what I did, you will find that any priest is capable of soloing Mor'Ladim.\
\
The basic strategy for a priest is to \"shackle-kite\" him. You want to open with a direct damage spell like mind blast or smite. Or, I suppose if you like, you could also try mind flay. Then once Mor'Ladim starts chasing you, shackle him. Get a little range, wait for some mana to regenerate, then re-open with another direct damage spell. \
\
A few things to note: If you constantly damage and shackle, you will probably run out of mana. So, you really want to wait for mana to regenerate during the shackle. Also, it might take you a little while to wear Mor'Ladim down with this strategy. But ultimately, you will able to solo him. If you have 5 talent points in shadow-weaving, you might be better off using mind blast so that the shadow vulnerability debuff stacks on Mor'Ladim. It's helpful, but not necessary. Also, since you are using shackle, I hope it is obvious that you don't want to do something like, Shadow Word: Pain Mor'Ladim. It will break the shackle for the duration. \
\
There is also a little court yard in Raven Hill Cemetary, which features a broken statue and a cobbled area around it. I found this to be relatively free from all the other monsters roaming the cemetary, and it's a good spot to shackle-kite Mor'Ladim. Just kite him to one side, shackle, and then run to the opposite side.\
\
Hope this was helpful.",
    "228173682201736822007/10/23 10:54:39wowisashMor'Ladim use to be 35 elite and he is around [b][16,38][/b] happy hunting",
    "228177554101775542007/11/01 04:06:41ClavsI soloed Mor'Ladim as a 30 Night Elf Hunter with my Tiger.\
\
You will need the time a freeze trap will buy you to get some mana and health back so have some bandages or a healing/mana potion ready to get back in quicker, then send your pet back in and let it get some aggro and start to fire away again.",
    "2281124420112442006/12/08 14:25:48LazebraitAlliance Side Only.\
Minimum Level Requirement: 28\
Notes: It would be wise to be partied up with others while doing this quest as the mob is an elite mob and could be exceedingly difficult to solo.\
\
Mor'Ladim can usually be found around the vicinity of the following co-ords. (16,38)\
\
Mor'Ladim seems to have a respawn time of 0-5 minutes.\
\
Completion of this quest will lead to \"The Daughter Who Lived\".",
    "2281830430183042006/12/28 16:44:19swotamThis quest rewards 150 Stormwind reputation as of patch 2.01.",
    "228113268101132682007/06/30 07:58:38GrieveI managed to solo him as a level 28 frost mage, the trick is to kite him over the clear patch of field between the house where Morbent Fel resides and the ghoul crypt, be sure to clear some of the Skeletal Raiders if you think they might aggro doing the job.\
\
Just pull him with your upper rank frostbolt, kite him with your lowest rank until you get a frostbite proc, then you cast your upper rank frostbolt again, when he gets withing range (often after he activates his 'special') just frost nova, take some distance and repeat the above strategy. When you reach the end of the field, do a quick turn, blink and start kiting him over the field again, the opposite direction.\
\
When you run out of mana, nova him and regen all your mana with evocate, then just continue on with the kiting. I did this without any twinked gear but I did use my Blessing of the Naaru in order to make sure I didn't die when I took two hits, so you might want to take a healing and mana potion doing this.\
\
I hope this helped, good luck on it, and enjoy your free experience for this awesome lore quest!\
\
(I recon other classes could do the same thing by just kiting him, or like Paryn gave the example for the shadow priest)",
    "2285286210528622007/03/17 20:39:30TheDiplomatsHe can be easily kited to darkshire or sentinel hill with a hunter/mage/warlock. When I did it at 28, he died right outside of town before any guards aggro'd on him.",
    "2281584820158482006/12/15 10:48:27NippurMorLadin is a tough undead. When you are fighting agains him, he attracts nearby squeletal healers and other undead, so it is wise to go with a party.\
In my case, I was able to kill him in 3 different occasions with a party of one healer lvl 33, two rogues (I was one) and a warrior.\
He respawns very quickly and he is extremely aggresive.",
    "2282932721142362007/02/02 07:08:15TenpastBut respawned a couple of minutes later.\
\
