    "3915002261460402007/03/12 09:36:12InfernoManSo in other words you didn't \"do\" the quest but had your friends run you through it?  This quest chain is not simple if you are doing it at the levels suggested for the quests.  My wife and I did this on our mages as we were leveling up, and the only suggestions I can give for the Stocks is be very careful about runners.  They will run when they are low on health so be ready to have a mage use frost nova or bolt, or some other form of stun.  If the runners escape and get into another room or down the hall from you, they will pull alot more mobs than you might be ready to deal with.  Other than that, this instance is very small and doesn't take too long to do.  \
   The resulting chain from this quest was very interesting in developing the story of the alliance and it's troubles.  I would recommend anyone who is starting out to do this quest, not have your friends do it for you, as the game experience you get from doing the quest (not just leveling xp) and the story is well worth it.  Also not to mention you will continue to develop your skills for working in a group which helps out alot in the later instances.",
