    "3917742830774282007/05/04 03:12:57LieandraNippur is incorrect about the gaurds helping you with the inmates. They do no such thing. \
\
Once you enter the instance. You fight the inmates that are within the instance. The inmates inside are Elites. \
\
The inmates that the guards outside of the instance fight (the ones that Nippur took a screen shot of) are not part of the instance. They are not Elite NPC's, and they don't even challenge you when they spawn. At least they have not challenged me. \
\
I tried several times to see if Nippur is correct. But he is not. I even killed one that walked past the instance portal, that I could not loot due to distance. When I went outside, he was gone. When I went back inside, he was still on the steps to far for looting.\
\
Just letting you know in case you have any ideas of doing this solo and thinking you can get help from outside the instance.\
\
Although. Running out the exit and then going back inside, resets the inmates. So if you agro a lot of them and make it outside. You don't have to wait to go back in.",
