  ["The Tome of Valor25"] = {
    "1652125npcDaphne Stilwell6182npcDuthorian Rall617125501165121652316534165451806165125npcDaphne Stilwell6182npcDaphne Stilwell618210001165121652316534165451806",
    "1652168743101687432007/10/15 00:14:15MagerificDaphne is at 41,89, It's passed the back entrance from Deadmines.\
\
I'd take a buddy with me If i was you. 3 waves of defias come at you. I believe the waves was 3, 4 and 5 of them.",
    "1652183745101837452007/11/13 21:25:33KseniyaSoloed as lvl 22 pally with a mana pot. Keep Consecration up and you're fine as long as you're careful with your heals.",
    "165248463048462006/11/27 13:46:59bensonfan9Catch the red eye back to stormwind\
\
http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6171",
    "165148452048452006/11/27 13:44:52bensonfan9During the fight three waves of defias thugs rush the house.  I believe it was 3, 4, then 5.  It was not a hard fight and if your health gets low cast a shield on yourself and you should be able to get two heals off without them being able to hurt you.",
    "1651209382102093822007/12/29 14:19:40GoronIs there a pre-req for this? My friend a level 21 Draenei Paladin cant seem to get the quest.",
    "1651140403101404032007/08/19 02:27:42ElodraiThis is the start of an important step for Paladins of the Alliance.\
\
You must Speak with Duthorian Rall and he will give you the Tome of Valor. Read the book and he will give you the next quest. The next step is to go to Daphne Stillwell in Westfall. (http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=6182)\
\
To get to her you have to go West towards the shore and past Daggerhills. This is the pass in the mountains where you had to kill a bunch of Defias. You have to go up to the exit of the Deadmines and go passed it until you see a house down a slope. Daphne is in the small field in front of the house.\
\
You will have to defend her against waves of Defias. It can be soloed pretty easily, heal Daphne to keep her alive while you dispatch the Defias.\
\
Upon completion, return to Stormwind to the trainer and you will receive your ability to Sense Undead and the shield Bastion of Stormwind (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9607)\
\
The paladin trainer will then instruct you to go to Jordan Stilwell. He is at the Gates of Ironforge (52,36). He will give you the quest The test of righteousness (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1653)\
\
This quest is putting you on the path of an important Blue two handed Mace that Paladins can use for a long time: Verigan's fist (http://www.wowhead.com/?item=6953#comments)\
\
 A great boost to all Paladins and highly recommended to invest the time to get it.",
    "16512521210252122007/01/26 16:32:42ataylorThe horde equivalent quest is The Second Trial (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=9690).",
    "16518211510821152007/05/12 23:37:10apeironAs stated above, it's a fairly simple tank and spank. Ret Aura, Righteous Fury, Consecration. I had Blessing of Wisdom in there, too. Having done main tank duty in DM a couple of times earlier that day, this was relatively child's play for a Prot spec. All melee, lots of Redoubt and Ret Aura love. Was almost too easy to solo at level 22. No special tactics other than my usual playing style.\
\
One important thing to note is that these Defias will NOT run away when their health gets below a certain point. You *can* Consecrate and Ret Aura them to death without having to chase them all over Westfall.",
    "16518262520826252007/05/13 23:47:04NycterisI would like to congratulate those who did this at level 20. I guess I suck at playing this class.\
I am a protection specced lvl 20 paladin and got killed all three times I did this quest. I can deal with the 3 man wave but 4 & 5 always get me.",
    "16514210910421092007/02/25 12:43:55AhkumTo find her, go to the Deadmines exit and follow the dirt path around back (not inside the cave, around the mountain.)  She will be in the orchard, and will walk to the house before the waves start coming.  The mobs are lvl 16-18 defias who were pretty easy to defeat, even for this undergeared just-turned-20 palladin.\
\
Tips:\
\
* Use Consecration early and often.  It just destroys them, and you get time to recharge your mana after each fight.\
\
* Use Retribution aura, as they hit fast but weak.\
\
* Kill with Daphne - Click on her, then press 'f' to get her target.  The mobs will go down much faster if you two are working together.\
\
* Use a board & sword (or mace, as the case may be.)  That extra defense and mitigation will come in very handy with all of their small strikes.\
\
I only had to shield once, and I probably could have even healed through that.  This should be pretty easy for most people.",
    "16511782270178222006/12/22 20:05:40OdoyleI did this solo at level 20 with green gear and 11 points into Holy. I failed it the first time but managed to do it on my second try. I have a few tips:\
\
First, use Retribution Aura. The Defias Raiders don't have a ton of HP, and it will weaken the rest down while you concentrate on one. The first time I tried and failed was with Devotion.\
\
Second, use Consecrate to grab initial aggro on the wave, and use it once or twice more during each fight. Same idea as Ret aura; it will beat all the Raiders down so by the time you get to the last one they will die in 1 or 2 hits.\
\
Third, fight close to Daphne. If you fight close enough to her she will run up and melee with you. Between Ret aura and Consecrate she won't pull aggro, but you could use Righteous Fury just to be safe =)\
\
Finally, bring some Melon Juice. You do get time to drink between waves but your time is limited.\
\
PS - Can't hurt to make sure LoH is up!\
\
Good luck to all =)",
    "1651211474102114742008/01/02 09:00:38AirslashThe quest begins as soon as you talk to daphne. She will run into the house to grab her gun. In the meanwhile you can hear the defias shout as they approach the house.\
\
The first wave is 3 raiders. You should be able to take them down fast by using the retribution aura combined with consecration. I was using a polearm at that time, but it pays of to have a shield equiped.\
\
The second wave consists of 4 raiders. This time you should use the same tactic, by using the retribution aura combined with the consecration on the ground. However, you need to stay really close to daphne to force her to fight with her sword. Assist her by selecting her and presseing the \"f\" button. If you attack the same target as her they go down faster.\
\
The third and last wave consists of 5 raiders. Same tactic as the previous wave. \
\
extras:\
popping bubble will cause the raiders to attack Daphne instead of you. You can use this as a breather to pick them of Daphne one by one in the last fight. If you attack them fast enough they can't kill her.\
\
You can rest between the waves. use this to keep you mana and health up.\
\
The quest fails once you release your spirit. So you can bring a friend along to ress you once you die. (haven't tried it yet)",
    "1651111190601111902007/06/25 19:30:58AntiprotonFor those new to this chain, make sure you talk to Duthorian Rall in the Cathedral of Light in Stormwind before going to find her. He had a *blue* question mark over his head when I went in, so I never bothered to talk to him. He gives you a book that starts the quest by sending you to find Daphne.",
  },
