    "2359198401982006/09/13 09:25:40UnlitPhoenixPretty easy quest, pickpocket the spikey hair undead for the key, stealth to the top of the tower and sap the elite, take the journal from the chest, and then run out or vanish (if you've learnt it already).",
    "2359209144102091442007/12/29 04:06:59ScragglylockThe chest in this tower is awesome for leveling up your lockpicking skill to 170. It can be used whether you've finished the quest or not... just use Lockpick instead of right-clicking. Keep in mind that it takes 3-5 seconds to repop, and it will give you the Touch of Zanzil debuff every time you open it. Happy hunting!",
    "2359189376301893762007/11/22 09:32:39kuromadAs of 2.3 there are no elites involved anymore. Not even klaven. So just whack them all.",
    "23592020930202092007/01/11 12:43:23pariversPickpocket the Malformed Lev24 Defias guard for the key. He patrols around the tower and is often alone, just wait for opportunity.\
\
Enter tower in stealth mode.\
Up one level is a guard stationed in center of pathway. Try to sneak passed her by walking up on the railing to the right (wait for patroling guard to be away).\
\
Even if you alert her, keep going to the right to next landing up. She will follow but you can easily kill her without alerting patrol guard. Stealth your way passed dual patrol on 3rd floor and make your way to top floor.\
\
Circle around to the right, chest is on floor near desk. Sap the boss, the open chest - take book - make a hasty getaway. Or wait for the boss to walk away from the table, or as mentioned above use distract. Open the box and then restealth. You can jump to first floor and run out - hopefully no guards patrolling out front, or stealth out again.",
    "2359164360101643602007/10/07 16:03:45jiyoungleI just want to verify that it is fairly easy to pickpocket the key, stealth all the way up to the top of the tower, sap the elite, and open the chest.  However, Touch of Zanzil seems to prevent stealth completely instead of just lowering it.  I've never played a rogue before this week so I don't know if this effect was different before.  I was trying to re-stealth but couldn't, so I jumped all the way down and sprinted out.  It occurred to me that I could probably remove the poison with my anti-venom (made through first-aid), which was the case.",
    "2359131137201311372007/08/02 14:24:45CybersonixYou get poisoned with Touch of Zanzil http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=9991\
Cure it by continueing the quest chain or by a druid, shamy, pala or anti-poison with first aid.",
    "2359190269201902692007/11/24 04:44:53royaleCompleting this quest also awards you the ability to craft and train Poisons.  You will learn Instant Poison upon turning in the quest, and can train future poisons at the rogue trainers.\
\
You don't need to do any other quests in this chain if you don't want to.",
    "23599830110983012007/06/04 22:02:17seanuWith the new patch Sap doesn't break stealth so just Sap then pickpocket the drone. Once you are inside stealth then just Sap the first guard on the ramp... wait for the patrolling guard next to her to patrol up the other ramp, then head up the opp. ramp and when you reach the next landing watch out for the two patrolling guards. Once past them just headed up to the top, go behind the elite and sap, then open the lock box to get the journal. Dont forget the poison that you get from the box lowers your stealth so you can move around as easy without being seen. Also if you have having trouble then if you read the journal then it clearly says that they bleed easly. So just Backstab, Sinister Strike, then Gouge and Rupture. Bleed them out. Dont be like me and aggro everyone on the way down. I died and had to go back up for the journal with the poison on me... it sucked. So i just took my Warlock and killed everyone.",
    "235917211017212006/10/10 14:43:58tokenIf you have your distract ability already you can use that instead of sap'ing the elite.  Worked fine for me.  Did the whole quest and didn't use my weapons once.",
    "235934382210343822007/02/11 23:56:54kanoWould just like to add that you NEED to have to trained your lockpicking to 70, or you won't be able to open it. The key you get from pickpocketing won't do the trick.\
\
This will probably save the confusion for rogues like myself that leveled in draenei areas to 20 and hadn't leveled up their lockpicking  in Redridge yet.",
    "2359166071301660712007/10/11 16:28:32shankaneggarOK, after u get the quest circle the tower until u see a spikey haired lvl 24 elite. go behind sap and pick him, easy enuff. now comes the hard part, go into the tower and up the first set of stairs. stop and look for a pat (should be a woman), get past her and go up the next set of stairs. there should be 2 pats that circle that room, wait til they go around and rush up the stairs (but don't unstealth) and sprint if u must but i wouldnt waste it. after u get into klaven's room its kinda smooth sailing from there. at lvl 20 u can basically go into the corner where the box is unstealth and pick it (but u need 70 lockpick). \
\
aftter u pick it u cant stealth bcuz of the poison so when u do this either bring a stealthed druid or run for ur life (thats wat i did). now is when sprint might be handy to u, but it wisely cuz if the malformed guy catches u ur dead ( he hits for 200s-250s) run out and if u die just make sure its outside the tower and then ur good for this quest. find a pally/ druid in sentinal hill to cure u and go hand that quest in and get ur poisons (dont worry about the poison curing quest unless u wanna do it but ur gonna have to talk to him u just dont have to do the quest.",
