    "470155535101555352007/09/20 07:59:55pbinkWow, this quest was not a wild goose chase for me.  All I did was make my way to the house that was cited in the coords above and there was a slightly reddish-colored ooze inside the tomb entrance.  Dropped the bag, no problem.",
    "470180340101803402007/11/07 02:40:06FurieslockThis has got to be one of the most easiest quests in the game, i have done this with 7 different charecters. I normally pick up the quest and on my way to Greenwarden i kill the oozes. It normally drops in the first 2-4 kills.",
    "4708763008762006/09/22 10:01:29GweedoI have a funny story to tell about this quest.\
\
On my last server, everybody told me to AVOID this quest because it was such a pain in the neck.  And it was.  It took me forever to get the stupid bag.\
\
A few months later I migrated to Gnomeregan and \"started over from scratch\".  I realized this morning that I hadn't done any of the Wetlands quests, and there was nobody from the guild on so I decided to load up on them and try to burn through them as fast as possible.  After visiting the Greenwarden, I was on my way to assassinate some gnolls when I saw a whelp and remembered that a beloved friend of mine in the guild wanted a whelpling pet, so I spent the next four hours farming whelps.\
\
I got the bag OVER THERE.  Like in the 60,40 neighbourhood.  NOWHERE NEAR where the quest says to get it from.  I was farming whelps when one of the larger oozes jumped on me and I killed it outta self defense and the bag dropped.  I just about died laughing.",
    "470175960101759602007/10/28 12:12:09AsearaGot the bag in about five minutes with the cords 42,27",
    "470170942201709422007/10/18 08:23:55adashielI think most of the bad feelings about this quest were from earlier in the game's history.  On my first couple of characters, this one quest took more time than any of the others in the Wetlands.  However, recently, perhaps in the past year, the drop has come very quickly.  I did it again last night and it dropped on my third kill.  The time before that I believe it was on my tenth.  That's certainly a lot better than the hundred or so it took the first couple of times.  I've heard similar reports from my guildmates, so I suspect Blizzard tweaked the drop rate at some point.",
    "470172244201722442007/10/20 13:30:50SurprincessDid this with my lvl 21 hunter, got the bag at the 2nd kill.\
So higher lvls (or the same lvls as the oozes are) might struggle with this... Guess the best lvl to do this is about 21-23.",
    "470179565101795652007/11/05 10:42:33AbolereReally not even that bad of a drop. I'd say 10 oozes - which are really easy to kill if you're 24+ - and you'll have it. Took me less than 10 minutes and I had it.",
