  ["Covert Ops - Beta22"] = {
    "10802219npcGaxim Rustfizzle4077npcGaxim Rustfizzle40772200Gnomeregan Exiles350",
    "10806649140664912007/04/13 08:20:04skyoverheavenJust to note, you don't actually need to use the explosives/detonator given in this quest, so if something goes wrong (ie: you took too long getting to the quest item and all the mobs went back) you can always clear to the quest item the old fashioned way. The item is right out in plain sight, so the explosives are just a fun and easier way to get the item.\
\
The mine is in the eastern portion of Windshear Crag, so work your way there and in front of the entrance, you'll see the wagon of explosives. Before setting the charge, look at the entrance of the mine, and in front of it (just to the right) you'll see a crate with a clickable item -- that's your quest item.\
\
As a hunter, here's how I did this: before setting the charge, I cleared the mobs to my left (along the mountain/hills) almost up to the quest item. Then I set the red charge on the wagon, moved a bit away (towards where I cleared) and then detonated the wagon. The mobs in the center/front will investigate the explosion, leaving a couple of mobs to clear. I sent my pet to both leftover mobs to distract them and looted the quest item, then ran away, calling my pet to retreat, back the way I came. The two mobs that aggroed chased me, and I killed them when I was at a safe distance from the mine.",
    "10801577260157722006/12/15 07:09:32ravenarkBoth quests are easy enough if you know when and where to pull. I did both of them by myself. If you are a druid or rogue, the best thing to do is prowl around the areas so you can get a good idea of where people are, where the plans and letters are, and where to run. \
\
Covert Ops Beta - This is a little more difficult than Alpha. The wagon for this one is on a small hill in front of the mine. The mine is located at about 74,58 or so. There are no guards on this wagon, just an operator, and he's far enough away where he won't aggro. Slightly behind the wagon there is a small hill. You can blow the wagon if you stand on that hill and keep the wagon to your right. \
\
The letters for this one are on the right/east side of the mine entrance, on a tree stump. They look like a stack of books. \
\
Here's the trick for this one...the kobolds don't run when you blow the wagon. So, you need to kill some of them before setting the explosives. On the west side of the mine, there is another small hill with three kobolds wandering. Take them out. On the east side of the mine, along the ridge, there are two other kobolds. Take them out too. There is another kobold closer to the letters, but if you attack him you'll draw the attention of everyone else, so leave him alone. \
\
Run over to the wagon (don't let anyone see you!) and set the explosives. Get over to the hill and set them off, then take off running. Head over the hill where you killed the first kobolds, then turn to the mine and get the plans. Then run AWAY from the mine (I went to the east, along the cliffs). The kobold you didn't kill will most likely aggro, but if you stop to kill him the rest of the Venture guys will be back and aggro. Just make sure your health is full and run along the cliffs. He stops giving chase soon.",
    "1080126902101269022007/07/26 00:46:50sanjaygfor dwarfs: find treasure works so use it",
    "10805483530548352007/03/21 13:10:52mjollinirthey run back to the mine pretty quickly after you blow the wagon, so move fast.",
    "10807442431157722007/04/28 13:09:26RenothActually the plans are not on a tree trunk instead they are on a crate box. I spent a great amount of time looking for these on a stump",
    "10807214331686452007/04/24 12:08:34LikeIkeCorrection:\
\
Prerequisites for this quest are:\
-Ineptitude + Chemicals = Fun (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1074)\
-Special Delivery for Gaxim (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1077)\
\
Covert Ops - Alpha (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1079) is offered at the same time as this quest, thus NOT a prerequisite.\
\
When both Alpha & Beta are completed, the next quest in line \"Kaela's Update\" (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=1091) will be available.\
\
Apologies for the mix up.",
