  ["Morbent Fel32"] = {
    "553224npcSven Yorgen311npcSven Yorgen3113850Stormwind5001952230326242655266645372688323926910270113211232413322143251555",
    "556593741573022007/04/12 08:10:39CabalI followed a similar method in soloing him with my Subtlety Rogue (who was L32 at the time). Instead of sapping Morbent, I opted for Ambushing his strongest guard (with a 3/3 in Imp. Ambush, he was down nearly half his health at the first strike). I killed each guard in turn, ignoring Morbent completely - which, yes, meant eating shadowbolts, so I did get pretty low on health by the end - and Vanished as soon as the last one was dead. This left Morbent alone, with me in Stealth mode right behind him.\
\
The 'Morbent's Bane' item has a 30-second cooldown when you first equip it, so no bandages are necessary; by the time the cooldown was complete, I was back to full health. Using the Bane aggros Morbent, so there was no chance to open with a sneak attack; fortunately, you don't really need one (just make sure to swap the Bane out for a real weapon right after you use it!). Without his guards, Morbent is easy meat: his physical attack is weak, and (as FirefoxUzi notes) his spells can be easily interrupted with Kick or Gouge. I threw Mind-Numbing poison on the slower of my blades, just to make his life extra-miserable... ;)",
    "55133429301334292007/08/06 19:12:29kelvinhe is a problem to kill on your own, \
\
there are 3 mobs downstairs, \
2 opposite the door,\
1 next to the stairs\
\
then another mob at the top of the stairs\
\
then Morbent Fel with 3 mobs in the next room",
    "55207027102070272007/12/25 10:41:17siriosThe quest is now really easy.Go in 17.33 in Raven Hill .You will have to kill 3 mobs that are seperate in the house.Then just go close to him and use Morbent's Bane.This will remove his shield and make him a non-elite mob.Really easy to kill :)",
    "554975120497512007/03/11 20:41:54AmanitaThis guy is a BEAR to kill. I am lv 43 hunter w/pet and teamed with a 29 warrior (I think) ... the guards are a pain to get at first. You will need (may need ...) some heals to get to kill him. One thing we both errored on was killing Morbent Fel BEFORE our visit to Sven that says \"bring Morbent's Bane to Sven\" ... I incorrectly thought that meant AFTER we killed him. WRONG! He basically wants to check out your weapon. You MUST see him also BEFORE you kill him ... or you will have to do it twice, like we did!! There was no special loot drop, no head, etc. Just his death to complete the quest, then a quick run back to Sven to finish up.",
    "556965531573022007/04/19 14:14:55IcemeltWish I had read this post first. Used vanish as you said, but died 3 times before my retard proc ended and I used the torch. Without the torch, I managed to get him down to 182 health, I see this as a great acomplishment seeing as how he went down so easy when I finally used the torch.",
    "555730230573022007/03/26 03:24:00FirefoxUziSoloed this as a 30 Combat Rogue. First I sapped Morbent, then moved around the corner and popped Blade flurry.  I was able to kill the adds, then vanish. I bandaged and went back in on Morbent.  I used the torch and swapped my weapon back in as soon as my shield was down.  He's really easy, a weak melee attack and a weak shadowbolt that you can kick/gouge.",
    "55114718301147182007/07/03 01:07:11FinallightHint: You can use a 2h weapon and have the \"Morbents Bane\" in your Inventory. Dont make the same mistake i did and try to lvl your Weapon skill with a 1h weapon just so u can use the bane in your off hand... dosnt work. And its a waiste of time.",
    "551743520174352006/12/19 15:58:16InfernoManThanks for the info on all the guards around MF, just a quick question..... How can you use an item that is a quest reward for completing this quest?  \
Quote: \"Also make sure you are using the torch of the holy flame. This will degrade MF's Armor enough to help you destroy him.\"  Thats the only thing that confuses me...",
    "55511410051142006/11/29 06:57:30XFGREAPERThree other guards are in the room with Morbent Fel. And one at the top of the stairs before you get to the room. pull the one from the top of the stairs then buff up and focus on the other 4. Pets and DOTS will help. Also make sure you are using the torch of the holy flame. This will degrade MF's Armor enough to help you destroy him. Soloing him may be an effort with out a pet. or being Lvl-60",
    "55174389201743892007/10/24 17:26:29listraitI was dreading this, but easily soloed it as a 34 hunter (after dying my first try, tried to take him out first).  You _must_ kill his 3 associates first, Fel himself doesn't pack much of a punch.  (YMMV, obviously most things're easier as a hunter, especially if you have \"Gift of the Naaru\")",
    "551841361174352006/12/29 02:21:41SibertankMake sure to keep the torch once you kill him, I destroyed mine once I had killed him. Had to abandon the quest and kill him again. Make sure to keep it to turn in!!!",
    "55192780201927802007/11/28 12:48:11foxwensoloed on a level 32 rogue...very easy.\
pull guard upstairs and kill\
