    "303185651211741782007/11/16 08:31:13adashielThere is nothing wrong with the story behind the quest.  There isn't even anything wrong with the difficulty of the quest.  What is problematic is the mechanics of the quest design itself.  [i]That[/i] is the \"WTF?\" I'm talking about.  If you are at the appropriate level for a run on the Stockade, it's unlikely you've been doing level 30 quests, elite or not.  If you are at the level to do this quest, it's unlikely you'll be interested in going back to the Stockade anyway.  A more appropriate location for Kam Deepfury would have been Gnomeregan, which also has a Dark Iron presence and follows quest level progression more naturally.",
    "303174178201741782007/10/24 09:04:50adashielThis is one of those \"WTF?!\" quests, not so much for its degree of difficulty, but because it is a prerequisite for a quest in a lower level dungeon.  Before you can pick up \"The Fury Runs Deep\", which is to kill the level 27 [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=1666]Kam Deepfury[/url] in [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?zone=717]the Stockade[/url], you have to kill [i]thirty[/i] level 27-31 Dark Iron dwarves in northern Wetlands.  By comparison, the similar quests to kill [url= http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=386]Targorr[/url] and [url= http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=377]Dextren Ward[/url] have no prerequisites at all.\
\
In 2.3 these dwarves will likely be non-elite, but it still doesn't make much sense as a prerequisite.",
    "303193054201930542007/11/29 00:59:47DiscombobulatorThis quest is still a pain in the ass post 2.3, at least if you solo it. You may get stuck needing 3 demolitionists and in the process clearing dozens of tightly packed (and still noticably dangerous) other dorfs that you don't need, will have to PRAY that demos spawn in each little nook and cranny. Unless you're a lock with Eye of Kilrogg you can't really see what's ahead in most of the buildings without pulling it. Escape can be tough once you've cleared your way in and the respawns outside the gates are back up.\
\
Just don't get bold thinking the 2.3 nerf is enough to solo this. Bringing a friend is advisable.",
