    "95042704340270432007/01/29 10:14:51randyzCoordinates are accurate and level is pretty accurate also (24) - you can do it at a lower level but you'll probably die a few times - the elementals here are 23/24 and unless you are lucky, you'll get two on you at some point.  By the way, they are in the water surrounding the island too. so watch out for those.",
    "9504131186301311862007/08/02 16:23:50arcoI died once, but that was just because I ran in without really looking around.\
\
The mobs aren't all that tough, but if you get more than one on you, you're probably going to die.  I ran in and managed to get the water, but died trying to escape.  Honestly, I just spirit rezzed and took my flight/boat back to Darkshore/Exodar, then flew back to Blood Watch.  It took about 10 minutes to make it back to Aqueous, so the resurrection sickness wasn't a big deal, and the 10% durability hit was worth it.",
    "950421046130210462007/01/17 12:54:27DagaraFound at 33,67 in Ashenvale.",
    "95045024620502462007/03/12 19:09:05iamgreySince it's very likely you will die doing this, you can also corpse-run it: Die, rez on top of the fountain which Kilrathi's screenshot shows: http://www.wowhead.com/?screenshot=view&5.9504#14025 and use the Bota Bag. It is channeled like a spell and will get slowed down by you getting hit but it is NOT auto-interrupted like herbing/mining. While you might have a hard time fighting the elementals, dying close enough you can rez on the fountain is fairly easy to do ;-]",
    "950415008511210462007/09/07 00:20:19apfhexTrue, but you need to know that you'll have to be higher than 20 or else you'll probably just die repeatedly (Stoneclaw Totem doesn't seem to work too well for distracting them while you gather the stardust).\
\
