    "13823086691178422007/02/04 21:01:41snuffedRemember to do Centaur Bounty (http://www.wowhead.com/?search=Centaur+Bounty) as well because which ever clan you're killing will drop the ears needed for that quest ... for me I only had 1.5 bars of rep to go to get to friendly when I got all 15 ears. another that makes this rep \"grind\" easy is that they only become hostile/aggroed (0 unfriendly) on the same kill as the last one that lvls you to friendly with whichever opposing clan.",
    "138214967131178422007/09/06 02:41:19TiranBoth start at 2000/3000 neutral. Takes 50 kills to get up the 1000 rep to 0/6000 friendly. The same 50 kills drop you 5000 rep for the other one, leaving you at 0/3000 unfriendly. They don't actually become hostile and attack you unless you kill one more centaur, or turn in this quest.",
    "1382168003101680032007/10/14 01:38:00FaaRThis quest (along with its counterpart for the Magram) signifies all that is faulty and wrong with Blizzard's reputation system. If you for whatever reason want to do this quest when the Magram mobs have gone \"grey\" - i.e. don't give any experience when killed - you will need to kill [B]*250*[/B] of them to reach friendly with the Gelkis...\
