    "685185047411750502007/11/15 11:13:39theZConfirmed as of patch 2.3 nerfed this quest, as well as all involving Stormgarde Keep.  Elites have been downgraded to normal :)",
    "685175050101750502007/10/26 07:14:21adashielThis is from a 44 protection paladin soloing, but should be useful for smaller or lower level groups as well.  It took me a few tries to get it right.\
\
Though linked to each other, Otto and Falconcrest are not connected to their guards.  I cleared out the mobs in the room in front of their stage, but didn't bother with the two guards up by them.  Then I took advantage of Falconcrest's higher level -- and thus larger aggro radius -- to proximity pull them to me.  I just edged up to the platform, and when Falconcrest (and thus Otto) aggroed, I retreated back into  the area I'd just cleared.  Their guards stayed put.\
\
Otto does less damage than Falconcrest, but because of his frequent interrupts, I killed him first.  When he gets low on health, he runs, but even when he ran through one of his guards, [i]they did not come to his aid[/i].  So I just let him go, turned on his boss, and then finished him when he came back.  Falconcrest doesn't really have any special tricks, but since he does hit very hard, taking him out was a very close thing.  If you have any way to mitigate his damage, it will help.  I went in with a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=4421]Scroll of Protection III[/url], [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=3826]Mighty Troll's Blood Potion[/url], and an [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?item=9206]Elixir of Giants[/url].  I started the fight with a [url= http://www.wowhead.com/?item=4623 ]Lesser Stoneshield Potion[/url] active and drank a [url= http://www.wowhead.com/?item=1710 ]Greater Healing Potion[/url].  All my cooldowns were up, of course.\
\
Note: I believe these guys are nerfed for 2.3, which should make a lot of the preparation you have to do now unnecessary.",
