    "1699165481201654812007/10/10 06:07:36bluewireI found some great tips somewhere else that helped a lot.\
\
The coords 20,27 are perfect.\
\
At level 21 (Warrior) I took the advice to scout the route, and clear a few mobs before taking the quest.  Go up the hill towards Bellygrub's garden, and then in the middle of the garden, turn right and climb the hill.\
\
I found 2 mobs on the plateau there, spread apart enough to kill one at a time.\
\
Going north, sticking to the left, I was able to avoid the small camp, and find the path heading up and left, between the rocks, just north of the tree.  This goes around the tent camp, and to the ravine leading to the cave.\
\
I found one mob in the ravine, and took him out.  I took out two at the cave door.\
\
Then ran back, mob free, got drunk, turned around and ran back to the cave.  I had to kill one mob on the plateau, and one just inside the cave, before going far enough inside to ding the quest, and then run home clean.  \
\
Just under 5 minutes - and only that long because the booze really is disorienting, and I took it slow to be sure I stuck to the right route.  There certainly was enough time in the hour available to clear the whole path, and also to wait for the booze debuff to wear off, but hey ... someone thought we should do it drunk, so that's how I wanted to try it.\
\
Excellent fun quest.",
