    "4349280310928032007/05/29 00:15:45laughingnomeI could only do this (as a mage 27) by enlisting someone to help me kill both of these guys. With two people, it is very easy - piece of cake. The other guy was a lvl 32 Paladin and had no idea what was going on since the quest is not sharable.",
    "43411495150114952006/12/08 16:48:45bangyThis is a really fun quest, and is part of a great series (starting from a drop off VC in Deadmines, leading to Stockades, then finally paperboy quests in SW) which leads to the great reward - seal of wrynn, an amazing ring which will last you until level 50.\
\
The quest invovles assasinating the boss of the traitors against Stormwind. As a rogue, mage,  warlock, hunter , this quest is easier because you can crowd control one (sap, sheep, pet, fear, etc). However, as a warrior you may find difficulties.\
\
A useful tip is to wave at the guards when they walk away. Because they are friendly, they wave back to you (they are the only guards who do) and stop walking. Keep waving until the speech is over and recorded. Then charge in, and do a decent amount of damage, Just before you die, pop a hp pot and run to the guards you were waving to. Because they waved back, they will not have gone far and will help you kill the 2 traitors.\
\
Make sure you get a decent amount of damage first though, or else you won't get the kill. You need to take at least 1/4 chunk of their hp bar before you can get a kill.\
\
keep /waving for all you're worth! Do this and you can complete the quest at around level 30. The key is taking the kill.",
