I picked up some water breathing potion knowing I would be trying this.\
I finished Magical Analysis.\
Got the quest Ansirem's Key (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=603).\
Flew to Booty Bay, tuned in Ansirem's Key quest.\
Got \"Pretty Boy\" Duncan quest (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=610).\
Did the \"Pretty Boy\" Duncan quest, turned it in.\
Got The Curse of the Tides.\
Went out there, drank a water breathing potion and cleared out all the murlocks near the altar.\
I then opened my inventory, right clicked on Catelyn's Blade, then clicked on the altar.\
I saw in the chat:\
Short Jon Mithril yells: Ah, hits the spot!\
Gazeban says: Oh now you've gone and angered me! Time to see the true force of the Stone of Tides!\
\
Gazeban showed up, I killed him and got the Stone of the Tides.\
\
Don't know if it will work for you, but it did for me.  Maybe it was because I didn't log out between certain stages, perhaps because I right-clicked on the blade, then the alter, no clue, but I hope it helps.\
Also while you're in the vicinity it's might be worth picking up 9 Blue Pearls for the Badlands quest Pearl Diving (http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=705).\
\
Good Luck!",
