    "1287204085102040852007/12/19 17:49:55speakhe's either bugged, or you can't pull him away from the tower and kite-kill him.  when you do get him down to 20%, he goes friendly like he should, but doesn't give any interaction gump.  no ? mark or anything.",
    "1286192019201920192007/11/27 04:14:26SticklebackAs a lvl 37-38 mage I tried this quest many times but always ran into problems with respawns.  In the end ran in to the tower & died.  Rez'd right at the very top of the stairs in the tower & managed to eat, drink & buff.  It kept putting me in & out of combat but Balos couldn't touch me. Once ready, moved close to Balos & easy kill.  Don't get too close to him though otherwise you pull 2 other mobs.  Ran out/blinked with mana shield on & job done.  I guess I could have done this to get onto the top of the stairs!  Good luck",
    "1286184676201846762007/11/14 21:56:25steelcobraIf you enter Lost Point without the quest, the deserters, save for Balos Jacken, will be green(friendly).  However, with the quest, they read as red (hostile).  They are close enough together to cause problems for a 41 Warrior solo.",
    "1286185796701857962007/11/16 13:55:31DraycanThe respawn rate on these guys was retard, I couldn't get anywhere near the tower without having the adds that I had just taken down respawn.  This is on patch 2.3.",
    "1286186393211857962007/11/17 14:48:42AltaurelThis quest is far too difficult for this level.  It's not worth the time.",
    "1286186432301864322007/11/17 15:48:46TrillessI did this on my 39 RET specced Paladin.  I believe the quest is a bit buggy.  I killed a path to the tower door, then Divine Protection I ran into the tower and up the short steps to the very end.  For some reason this reset all the aggroed mobs.  Balos will return to the small landing on the stairs.  Killed him solo.  Returned to top of stairs.  For some reason this is a safe zone of sorts.  Waiting on DP timer... then ran out.\
\
Hope that helps some of you ^^",
    "1286209562102095622007/12/29 20:52:47shammanNo deaths needed, just a bit of stamina. I tried a few times to fight my way in but the mobs respawned far too fast to keep up with them - got about four down before the first came back at me because I was still in his aggro range.\
\
Completed it after reading the above, but without dying. Run in and veer slightly to the left, run up the slope and onto the steps behind Balos, and the mobs start evading. From these wooden steps I was able to step off them and burst Balos down before stepping back on them to make the others to evade again. Once Balos turned friendly I could complete the quest from the steps and accept the next part before running out.\
\
Note for shammies: I managed to use ghostwolf while stood on the wooden steps so ran out in that form, never though to use it on the way in though as I figured it would be 'indoors' anyway.\
\
Have uploaded some screenshots, they should be there once approved.\
\
EDIT\
\
3900xp from handing it in at Balos",
    "12861652110165212006/12/17 13:05:48kreghxThe tower containing the Theramore Deserters is south from the Shady Rest Inn. Take the road east from the Inn and take the first road that leads south. The tower is very near the road on the left, or the east side of the road. Cosmos loc is 35,54.",
    "12867600910760092007/05/01 10:21:40sharnlaWhen you go inside the tower, Balos Jacken will immidiately aggro (just one 38 mob).",
    "1286197632101976322007/12/07 20:35:42wvaughn78109Did on my 41 rogue, actually forgot about it, stealthed in, beat Balos into submission, only had one add.  He went to get help so I vanished.  Easy if you can stealth, watch the add, he will get help.",
    "1286193742211920192007/11/30 03:58:40deathonabunDid this on my 39 mage: mana shield, run to the top to the broken stairs, wait for mobs to reset, eat/drink, fight the dude, complete the quest then mana shield and run out. Stickleback, you are the man!",
    "1286195141101951412007/12/02 22:57:09grawssYeah, at 1% health and ready to die, all the mobs went into evade mode. They cannot attack you on the edge of the steps. So run through all the mobs, into the tower, and once you get to the end of the steps just wait for them to reset. Once they do, edge down until Balos attacks. Kill him, then run out. If you get too close to Balos, you'll aggro a mob or two below, so stay near the wall and as near the steps as possible.",
    "1286189069201890692007/11/21 19:20:18clarkkersOkay, I did this as a 36 Enhancement Shammy.  I ran past Balos  up the steps (stops right behind) him and died.  I reincarnated and by some miracle was able to keep myself alive to finish the quest.\
\
Otherwise, i wouldn't be able to reach Balos  before repops get me.",
    "1286198094101980942007/12/08 15:10:39luckyshroomI tried this quest today on my 37 priest found it very hard to do.  At one point i got pissed and just ran in there and found out that if you stand at the top of the stairs just above Balos they can not attack you.  I healed up and moved down far enough that he wouldnt evade my spells and had no problem with the other NPCs in the tower.  Quest complete.",
    "1286187081311857962007/11/18 14:02:29oewasmandRespawn rate is crazy high indeed. Even inside the tower, respawns would appear while I was stil clearing it (with just 4 mobs inside!). Together with the fact that they run away to get help once they're below 10% health makes this quest rather difficult. I really recommend doing this in a pair.",
    "1286189809101898092007/11/23 05:36:48VoodumDid this on my level 37 hunter. I used Eyes of the Beast on my pet and had him aggro the entire room. I then ran up the steps past the npc and feigned death on the broken steps. I then stood back up and res'd my pet. I was then able to sit there evading all of his attacks until I was at full hp / mana. I then walked down onto the steps and fought him. Easy if you can make it to the broken steps no mobs can hurt you.",
    "1286282710028272006/11/04 12:37:29KaynosLost Point is at 35.53.  He doesn't mean SE of the Inn in Theramore, but SE of the burned Shady Rest Inn.",
    "1286205503102055032007/12/22 10:32:22WasabiiI tried this as a lvl 36 prot pali 2k/2.5k health/armor (respectively). Stupidly I didn't  read EVERY comment just where it was. I pull 3. 3 melee mobs vs 1 prot pali is just ezmode.  3 more mobs aggro some how and one runs for help.\
\
So I pull them to the road LoH to live, then drink/eat up. I head toward the tower  pull one guy walking around and another I SWEAR I just killed. Then the fun started they started to respawn as I was fighting it was then about 8-10 on one...needles to say I was a dead pali.\
\
I was about to try the run up and talk but as I'm typing this a son of hakkar looking mob ate my face and now I need ot repair.",
    "1286205689102056892007/12/22 17:15:19VrtsmanI ended up getting killed and then when I went back to body to resurrect, I just stood behind Balos Jacken.  Don't have to kill him, just get him below 20 or 25 % and he'll turn green to finish the quest.",
