    "1143118365101183652007/07/10 00:45:04CelovekWhew!  I just soloed this as a 31 shaman and I had to do more graveyard runs than I'd like to admit.  The warlocks do run around a lot, so the challenge is to pull them away from other enemies, or else they'll pick up adds.  Of course, they're casters, and it's in tight quarters, so while you try to pull them away, chances are they'll be tossing shadowbolts at the back of your head. \
\
I suspect ranged characters (nukers and hunters) will have better luck with this place.  They can CC the voidwalker pets if need be, and then just out-DPS the warlocks.  The warlocks don't run around, I assume, if you're not getting up into melee range. \
\
Oh, and the boss guy is just a plain ol' warrior type; no specials that I saw.  Easy as pie.",
    "11431839420183942006/12/28 22:27:15swotamThis quest rewards 250 Darnassus reputation as of patch 2.01",
    "11436203121183942007/04/04 13:48:03CrystalisThis quest is a pain solo as a 29th level druid.  The warlocks constantly run out of melee range, drawing adds and their shadowbolts can cause damage, once they've got another warlock or two casting them at you while their voidwalkers gnaw at your back.  To top it off I think the respawn timer is something like 60 seconds as I would kill two, die, come back, and the first one was back already.",
    "1143150918101509182007/09/09 11:41:24ExsismJust soloed as 29 hunter.\
\
the trick for me was to kill the 2 warlocks at the bottom floor, always send pet in first. After that i had no trouble walking in withouth aggro, use eyes of the beast to control your pet, walk him up to the first warlock then let him run down far enough for you to be in line of sight. Do this all the way up, i had no trouble doing this, not even with the top level, i could easily get the 2 at the stairs, regain health and mana.\
Last thing, send your pet to one of the warlocks next to Athrikus, this will also aggro him, but that's allright as long as you remember to slow down the warlock so it doesn't run !\
Kill the warlock, then Athrikus and last the voidwalker, and voila you've got the head. No harm done :)",
    "11438019020801902007/05/09 04:52:59doramilCan be found at 56,26",
    "1143208558102085582007/12/28 04:12:05brasshopperI tried this several times and finally soloed it at level 35, as a priest. It was still yellow. At L30, the two warlocks at the base of the tower were still able to combine and kill me. Tonight the right warlock would just evade, but I think that I could have taken the pair.\
\
The warlocks will always attack before their minions. Routine was shield, dot, dot, manaburn, manaburn, wand if needed. re-shield, dot, wand the minion.  Only one warlock would attack at a time. I was able to single pull all warlock/minion pairs, just walking around the tower. If I could not easily target the warlock, I would let them attack to establish a target, as the warlock would always attack before sending their pet.  If you attack from a distance with a spell or probably an arrow, attacking the warlocks adjacent to Athrikus did not aggro him, although that might have been a level thing - a lower level might have a higher aggro radius.  In any case I never want to go into that silly tower again, at least with this toon.  \
\
There were respawns before I started down the tower. I could go down one stair while they were on the other without aggroing and kill the ones I had to. I would not do that on the way up because I was worried about him calling his minions for help but there had already been repops on the lower levels that did not interfere.",
    "1143206423102064232007/12/24 07:14:19tizz66Easy to solo as a Mage. Be sure to use Counterspell on the warlocks to reduce damage. They'll then run towards you to melee, so frost nova them and their minion, then DPS. Repeat for each. Just be careful of the threat from counterspell, although I didn't have any problems.",
