    "253108650101086502007/06/21 12:27:09druhimSolo'd her with my 30 hunter and my 30 kitty pet. Had to try several times because her body kept disappearing before I could loot it. I finally decided to loot it right after she died even though the skels got me, at least I got the heart finally and completed the quest.\
\
I should clarify that her body disappeared very quickly even when I lived through her and her guards. Her body had disappeared in less than a minute after killing her that time, so loot her as soon as she goes down.",
    "25361422150614222007/04/03 05:44:06ParynAs a level 33 shadow priest, I believe it's possible to solo Eliza. I (as a level 33 shadow priest) was able to bring her to around 80% health, before a random Shaman jumped in to help and finish her off. But, to be honest, I did not need any help.\
\
Here is the synopsis of the strategy I used:\
1) Run a little distance from grave after opening. \
2) Shackle Eliza.\
3) Mind blast Eliza.\
4) repeat step 2\
\
Here is the strategy in a little more detail.\
\
As many people have already mentioned above, Eliza does two things: She will cast frostbolt / frostnova and during the encounter she will summon three undead guardians, whom I believe are level 29. \
\
Because she will try to frostbolt you when you are out of melee range, the basic idea of my strategy was to cast a direct damage spell on her, then immediately shackle her before she can finish casting frostbolt.\
\
The shackling has the affects of interrupting her spell casting, allowing you some time to regenerate mana, and preventing her from summoning her undead friends.\
\
That's basically all there is to it. When she's shackled, she can't summon her friends. When she's casting frostbolt, she can't summon her friends. \
\
A few things to note. You want to cast a quick damage spell, like mind blast or smite. If you mind flay, you will probably not have the time to shackle her before her frostbolt finishes casting. You also don't want to use a spell like Shadow Word: Pain, for obvious reasons (You are using shackle!). You also probably want to wait for the \"Five Second Rule\" http://www.wowwiki.com/Formulas:Mana_Regen#Five_Second_Rule to fade so that you regenerate some mana. Else, if you decide to spam shackle / mind blast, you run the risk of running out of mana. \
\
Good luck.",
    "253119431201194312007/07/12 07:29:44CelovekHah!  Nuking her from the roof works indeed.  I was able to take her out this way, solo, as a 33 shaman, specced Enhancement (no nuking bonuses).  I put down a frost resistance totem and a mana spring and just kept lobbing Lightning Bolts at her.  I neglected to keep Lightning Shield up, but I imagine it would help significantly. \
\
I tried a more legitimate approach twice before, but wasn't able to take her out before her three guards took me out.  \
\
One odd thing I found was that, while on the roof, if you let up on the damage for a few moments too many, she leaves 'combat mode' and her health and mana shoot back up to 100%.  I found this puzzling, as I was still within range of her, but oh well, no biggie.  Just let your mana recharge and try again.",
