    "540188820217312007/11/21 10:38:25NescientAs of Patch 2.3, the ogres are no longer elites; however, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?npc=2417]Grel'borg the Miser[/url] is still elite (need to kill for [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=543]quest[/url]).",
    "540161297117312007/10/01 10:35:00DarthRahnDid as lvl37 warrior. You cannot take the book through the wall anymore; however I just came inside the house and casted intimidate shout. It lasts 6 seconds and you shouldn't cast it in melee range with him!!! 6 seconds is ok to take the book.",
    "5407312107312006/09/19 18:04:20peeweeswedenThis quest is easily soloable as lvl 34, regardless of your class. I've done it as rogue, druid, warrior and hunter. As rogue and druid it's of course easier, since you have stealth, but the way you do it is basically the same: \
\
Enter the ruins from the WEST, not on the road. Go to the Growless cave (38,68) and continue around the ruins clock-wise. There are some lvl 32-34 yetis roaming there, no big deal. Avoid or crush. When you are directly west of the ruins you will see a part of the wall with a hole in it. Enter there and very very carefully negotiate the ogres in there. They are 38-39 elites. I walk along the northern-most mountainside inside the compound. Your goal is *not* the main building, but the smaller house with a belltower. There is one ogre that'll probably aggro on you. If he does, run behind the target building and continue along the mountainside until he drops, or simply stand behind the house and let him smash you. Resurrect on that spot, behind the house. \
From above, the house looks like a \"T\" with a short base. \
\
X marks the spot you're looking for. Move the cursor along the wall until you see it shift into the \"use\"-cursor. That's the bookshelf you're looking for. Simply right-click it to get the book, right through the house wall! Negotiate your way out from the compaund the way you came. If you get aggro, make a run for it and die in a good spot (there is a space in the wall you got through at its northen-most end where you can exit and the ogres won't follow you outside)\
\
Still works with 1.12 as of Sep 20th 2006.",
    "540109408201094082007/06/22 15:14:47isolatiaA really easy way for rogues is to sneak in as close to the bookcase as you can, Blind the Ogre, quickly loot the book and hit Vanish.",
