    "4651853670185362006/12/29 20:09:42TetrisThe catapults are at 47,47 in Wetlands.  Just click on the one catapult and you will go through a quest dialog that leads to the next quest.",
    "465114922101149222007/07/03 11:03:00psycoticThis quest is soloable by a 29 feral druid.  As well as the following one.  Just pick your targets wisely and be sure to run if you get more than expected.",
    "465121962211149222007/07/17 02:21:14kaTTooThis quest was a breeze.  Almost \"too easy\".  My advice as well is, choose your targets wisely around the catapults. Take your time while taking the mob guards out.  Watch out for the shadowcasters, however, as they can catch you off guard.  Of course, should you engage one, you'll need to take care of him and his skeleton minion to proceed. \
\
Nek'rosh is down the hill from the catapults in a kind of fortress of the hills.  You can kill him fairly easily by vaulting the hills around him and coming at him from behind.  (Watch for guards on top of the hills and at least one shadowcaster on one side up higher). Pull Nek'rosh from behind and you will most likely only pull one or two of the guards, at most, with him.  I was able to pull him away from the surrounding mob with a couple of range shot arrows; then got him alone on top of the hill behind his garrison.  \"Chieftain\" Nek'rosh gave me a fight, but nothing that my lvl 30 warrior couldn't handle. \
\
Have fun with this one.  :-)",
    "465195661201956612007/12/03 22:41:36drakaSince patch 2.3, quest objectives like the catapults will appear on your minimap as little golden question marks so coords aren't all that necessary. The mobs were very, very tightly packed behind the quest objective catapult, so even though they were level 23-ish, there were at least six together. I was a little worried. However, I managed to inch close enough to the catapult to finish and pick up the next quest without aggroing any of them.\
\
Edit: I went back later and the mobs were more spread out around the catapult (like they should be), so I don't know why they were huddled together in one spot the first time I went. At least they're pullable when spread out a bit.",
