On an unrelated topic: This quest leads to http://www.wowhead.com/?quest=976.",
    "9736188131460542007/04/04 06:32:57BelazorIt's possible to pull the Felslayers without aggroing the \"boss\". Just wait until they are furthest away from him.\
\
Semi-related: Soloed as a 23 Rogue (Alchemist so had Str, Health and Armor pots on me).\
<< The summoning spell cannot be interrupted by Kick >> so save your cooldowns for the next Shadow Bolt.\
Ended the fight with 78 HP, so you might want to bring potions, bandages, escape mechanisms (Vanish) or a friend.",
    "973189401101894012007/11/22 10:21:00VeraldisThis quest is trivial for a rogue.\
\
Stealth past the various demons until you get to the ramp leading up to the shrine. There will be two lesser felguards along the path to the top; best to kill them just in case. There will be two felhounds near Ilkrud that can be pulled alone if timed right.\
\
Sap Ilkrud and take on the succubus; backstab if you have daggers, cheap shot if you've gotten the skill. She has very little hp's and dies quickly.\
\
Now, for Ilkrud. I opened with a backstab and tried to kick him when he summoned minions, but that didn't work. Gouge works, but Ilkrud immediately begins casting again, so you're still likely to get his demons. They're only level 17, though, and easily killed.",
    "9734605410460542007/03/04 14:55:11AdonaiHas a lvl 24 or so succubus pet and also summons 2 level 17 voidwalkers, not to mention that there are 2  (level 23 or 24) felslayers that seem to be linked to him. Either come with 2 people, a bit higher level and recommended, or pull a felslayer, kill it super fast, reset him and then do the same with him. Those are probably the best options.",
    "973162960301629602007/10/04 17:28:23HighFiveAs a [b]Hunter[/b] you can use your pet to tank him and the voidwalkers he summons, while keeping his succubus in a [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=1499]Freezing Trap[/url].\
\
As a [b]Priest[/b] you can [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=8122]fear[/url] him and his succubus when he starts summonning. Use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=3747]Power Word: Shield[/url] if you need to heal.\
\
As a [b]Mage[/b] you can [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=2139]Counterspell[/url] him(not sure if it would work, someone said that Rogue's [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=1766]Kick[/url] didn't and it's basically the same thing).\
\
As a [b]Warlock[/b] you can use your Voidwalker to tank them, [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=19438]Sacrifice[/url] him before he dies, and finish Ilkrud quickly. If you're level 28 you can also [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=710]Banish[/url] his succubus but you probably won't need it.\
\
As a [b]Warrior[/b] you can use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=72]Shield Bash[/url] to interrupt his casting(if it works) or use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5246]Intimidating Shout[/url] [i][u]after[/u][/i] he summons, since chances are he'll just start casting again after it wears off if you interrupted him with it.\
\
As a [b]Rogue[/b] you can [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=6770]Sap[/url] him and kill his succubus, use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=1777]Gouge[/url] to interrupt his summonning and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5277]Evasion[/url] if you can't kill him before he summons. After you kill him you can just [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=1856]Vanish[/url].\
\
As a [b]Paladin[/b] you can interrupt him with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5588]Hammer of Justice[/url]. You can also use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5599]Blessing of Protection[/url] and heal if you need to.\
\
As a [b]Druid[/b] you can use [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=5211]Bash[/url] and [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=16979]Feral Charge[/url] to interrupt him. A druid on this level wouldn't be able to heal with anything other than [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=2090]Rejuvenation[/url] unless talanted with [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=17068]Nature's Focus[/url].\
\
As a [b]Shaman[/b] you can figure it out yourself, since I have never played a Shaman above level 18 and should not suggest anything :)\
\
[b]edit[/b]: As a [b]Concerned Poster[/b] you can correct me when suggesting the impossible, such as using [url=http://www.wowhead.com/?spell=6770]Sap[/url] on a demon.",
    "9737272931460542007/04/25 12:50:14Crakieeasy to pull Felslayers\
\
Sap Illkrud --> Kill Minion --> Kll Illkrud (He summons Succubusses) retain Attackpower on Illkrud and vanish/fein Death as he dies the Succubusses will die.",
    "973108025201080252007/06/20 14:21:32CatalyzeI just did this quest as a 22 Hunter. The area to get to him is mostly level 22 - 24 demons. The area to get to him is shaped like a \"U\". You can come in either end of this but the path up the hill to him is at the bottom of the \"U\". The patrols are singles with an occasional felhound and felguard pair. I just used a freeze trap on the pairs with my pet on passive and pulling both to me and freezing one. Once you start up the short hill path, there is a felguard at the top. He is not linked to anything and you can pull him down the path safely. Go to the top of the path and look at the camp area where you will find the boss in the middle and his succubus next to him. In front of him on each side is a felhound (fellslayer is the name I think). They are NOT linked to anything. Wait until each one paths as far from the boss and just range pull each one back near the top of the path you just came up. Now you are faced with just the boss warlock and the succubus. I laid a freeze trap at my feet, hunter's mark on the boss, and sent my pet onto the Succubus next to the boss. I poured everything I had onto the boss and killed him as he summoned 2 voidwalkers. The succubus was at half health and so was my pet so I focused fire on her as 1 of the voidwalkers hit the freeze trap. The voidwalkers do very little damage so I ingnored the remaining one until the succubus was dead. The pet immediately attacked the voidwalker on me and I wing clipped it and ran to range. We killed it and the one just breaking out of the trap. My pet was at half health and so was I. There was no need to bandage or use a pot for me during the fight. I realize that every class fights differently, this is just a post to let you know what to expect when you do it. Good luck and stay safe.",
  },
